## How It Works\
\
### Recruiter Workflow\
1. Recruiter opens `/availability`\
2. Adds time slots (e.g., \'932026\uc0\u8209 07\u8209 20 10:00\'94)\
3. These slots appear in the booking page\
\
### Candidate Workflow\
1. Candidate opens `/book`\
2. Selects a slot and enters name + role\
3. Slot is removed from availability and stored as an appointment\
\
### Rescheduling Logic\
- Candidate enters their name  \
- Selects a new slot  \
- Provides a reason  \
- System checks:  \
  - Has the candidate already rescheduled?  \
  - Is the new slot available?  \
- If valid, the appointment is updated and the old slot is returned to availability\
\
